{"lemma":"قَدِيرٌ","slug":"قَدِيرٌ","root":"ق.د.ر","root_slug":"ق-د-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ق-د-ر","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"قَدِير","root":"قدر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":45},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n35291"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%82%D9%8E%D8%AF%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%B1%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"possessing power, possessing strength, powerful, potent"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"able"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"having mastery over"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"capable, competent"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"all-powerful, omnipotent, almighty"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare قَدَرَ (qadara, “to possess strength”)."},"ipa":["/qa.diːr/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n35291","headword_ar":"قَدِيرٌ","root":"qdr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAdirN","text_ar":"قَادِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  Flesh-meat"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cooked in a pot, with seeds to season it, such as pepper and cuminseeds and the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, JK:) if without such seeds, it is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TabiyxN","text_ar":"طَبِيخٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Lth, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is cooked in a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qidor","text_ar":"قِدْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (L, K:) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAdirN","text_ar":"قَادِرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": so in the K; but this seems to be a mistake, occasioned by a misunderstanding of the saying of Sgh [and others] that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qadiyrN","text_ar":"قَدِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAdirN","text_ar":"قَادِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": or perhaps the right reading of the passage in the K is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAlqadiyru AlqaAdiru wamaA yuTobaxu fiY Alqidori","text_ar":"وَالقَدِيرُ القَادِرُ وَمَا يُطْبَخُ فِى القِدْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and it has been corrupted by copyists:) (TA:) [but this is improbable, as the passage, if thus, would be in part a repetition:] also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cooked"},{"kind":"text","text":"broth; (L;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maqoduwrN","text_ar":"مَقْدُورٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (JK, L.)"}],"source_refs":["Lth","JK","TA","L","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}